    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Gunnar Henderson** stands as our premier offensive anchor with a score of 81.88. Even against a savvy pitcher like Lugo, his leadoff spot, dynamic platoon advantage, and elite skill profile make him a must-start. **Andy Pages** is our secondary force at 74.43; he draws a significant boost from an elite 5.04 xERA matchup and a stadium environment that favors his profile by 14%. Additionally, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Drake Baldwin** (71.27) benefit from favorable pairings against Elder and Irvin, respectively. These four represent the core of our daily ceiling, as each possesses the specific combination of batting order security and favorable starter matchups required to maximize our 5x5 output.\n\nThe decision to bench **Nolan Schanuel** was the tightest call on today\u2019s sheet. With a score of 46.58, he sits firmly in the marginal tier; while his 3-hole placement provides stability, the looming threat of Cease\u2019s 3.58 xERA effectively neutralized his upside compared to the higher-scoring alternatives in our outfield and utility slots. We are also monitoring the status of **Kyle Tucker**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, and **Jackson Merrill**, all of whom are unavailable today due to schedule gaps or rest, limiting our rotational flexibility. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (55.26) remains in the lineup, his score is tempered by a challenging matchup against Detmers, requiring him to rely on his strong underlying xwOBA to provide value. We will keep a close watch on **Nasim Nunez**; despite his 53.38 score, his spot at the bottom of the order and the scarcity of steals in this league make him a high-variance asset that we are prioritizing strictly for his speed profile.",
